 A veterinary doctor, Nuhu Madaki, has cried out after he was allegedly detained by men of the Nigerian Police Force along Edo/Kogi Expressway. According to Madaki, one Sergeant Odina Samson with Force number 388166, demanded money from him for no reason. After he was prevented from leaving, he was forced to deposit N2,000. It a post on his Twitter handle, Madaki said, “At the check point, they forced me to make a transfer and won't let me go until they get confirmation. “I was there for over two hours in the middle of nowhere.”